    "body": "I would have been ok with all this, if you'd just said that you're busy and you'd follow up in the future about it. \r\n\r\nBut I felt through our interactions that you'd already dismissed my ideas out of hand. You didn't even give guidance on how I myself could have helped to move things forward via a more realistic benchmark. \r\n\r\nI think if you were more serious in nurturing potential contributors, you'd have taken some time to at least reply. But its obvious the team is too caught up in whatever its doing.\r\n\r\nThis codebase is by far not the best in the world. Even then, I was willing to ignore it if it meant that Ethereum community can have less issues with state access bottleneck in the future. \r\n\r\nBut obviously, this was not welcome at all.\r\n\r\nIf you want to know - yeah, I am insulted. I've got many better things to do with my time than waiting around on no response and not being taken seriously. You guys needa get off your high horse. All your followers - they know nothing about how rotten geth is on the inside. I do, and with this kind of community spirit, I'm honestly done. Anyone would be.",
