    "body": "> So is this now stale?\r\n> \r\n> In the original PR @jon-chuang claimed a 3x improvement:\r\n> \r\n> > If this allows block construction time to be reduced by 3x, I would say this is a big win. It would also be robust and thus able to increase block gas limit by, hypothetically, 3x.\r\n> \r\n> Surely this is at least worth doing a proper benchmark on. Even a 10% increase would be significant.\r\n\r\nPlease see https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/22881#issuecomment-848862890. The PR OOMs, but before doing so, it is 12% slower than master. This was our problem all along, it's a blind optimization that the author didn't even bother to test on a live node. Can it be made faster? Maybe, I don't know. It is not my task to prove the PR is faster than one we have, that lies at the author.\r\n\r\nPS: Next time you want to contribute to the \"worlds shittiest codebase\", at least don't submit an OOM. Doesn't make you look good.",
